        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 7:16PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 716 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Us-190 Near The Menard-Mcculloch County Line, or 8 miles northeast
of Menard, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Melvin.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
